org.hanns.demonodes.privateParams

Class SetPrivateParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ros.node.AbstractNodeMain
      • ctu.nengoros.time.AbstractTimeNode
        • org.hanns.demonodes.privateParams.SetPrivateParameters
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.ros.node.NodeListener, org.ros.node.NodeMain

    public class SetPrivateParameters
extends ctu.nengoros.time.AbstractTimeNode
    Just a simple ROS node computing value of equation: y=a*sin(b*t), where parameters a,b and shouldLog can be set from the command line as follows: ./runner org.hanns.demonodes.privateParams.SetPrivateParameters _a:=11 _b:=10 _shouldLog:=true Note that in case of restarting node without parameters, the original ones are still stored on the parameter server, so they will be set according to actual values in the parameter server (ros core).
